From: Florian Westphal <fw@strlen.de>
Subject: [PATCH] subflow: check parent mptcp socket on subflow state change

This is needed at least until proper MPTCP-Level fin/reset
signalling gets added:

We wake parent when a subflow changes, but we should do this only
when all subflows have closed, not just one.

Schedule the mptcp worker and tell it to check eof state on all subflows.

Only flag mptcp socket as closed and wake userspace processes blocking in poll
if all subflows have closed.

